orities%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20deeply%20saddened%20by%20the%20loss%20of%20any%20marine%20life.%20We%20have%20comprehensive%20measures%20in%20place%20to%20help%20avoid%20collisions%2C%20such%20as%20training%20all%20our%20deck%20officers%20with%20the%20Ocean%20Research%20%26amp%3B%20Conservation%20Association%20(ORCA)%20and%20we%20follow%20regulations%20designed%20to%20protect%20whales%20and%20other%20marine%20life.%20This%20includes%20altering%20itineraries%20in%20certain%20regions%20to%20avoid%20whales%20and%20we%20will%20continue%20to%20evaluate%20and%20update%20our%20procedures%20with%20our%20partners%20and%20the%20authorities%2C%20''%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERob%20DiGiovanni%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20chief%20scientist%20of%20the%20Atlantic%20Marine%20Conservation%20Society%2C%20told%20The%20Post%20it%20was%20more%20than%20likely%20that%20the%20''interaction%20with%20the%20vessel%20contributed%20to%20her%20death.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fisheries.noaa.gov%2Fspecies%2Fsei-whale%5C%22%3ENational%20Oceanic%20and%20Atmospheric%20Administration%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0Sei%20whales%20can%20grow%20to%20be%20up%20to%2060%20feet%20long%20and%20have%20a%20lifespan%20of%2050%20to%2070%20years.%20They%20are%20known%20as%20exceptionally%20fast%20swimmers%2C%20capable%20of%20reaching%20speeds%20of%20more%20than%2034%20miles%20per%20hour%20(55kph).%C2%A0They%20dwell%20mostly%20in%20subtropical%2C%20temperate%20and%20subpolar%20seas%20around%20the%20world%2C%20primarily%20the%20Atlantic%2C%20Indian%20and%20Pacific%20oceans.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThese%20whales%20used%20to%20be%20abundant%20in%20the%20US%20and%20around%20the%20world%2C%20but%20up%20to%20300%2C000%20of%20them%20were%20killed%20by%20commercial%20whalers%20in%20the%2019th%20and%2020th%20centuries%2C%20according%20to%20NOAA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715251080000%2C%22visual