transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Natalie%20Fischer%2C%2025%2C%20from%20Washington%2C%20about%20her%20experience%20in%20a%20%26quot%3BDINK%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20double%20income%2C%20no%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20relationship.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20husband%20Keldon%20and%20I%20first%20got%20together%20in%20January%202018%2C%20we%20knew%20we%20weren't%20ready%20to%20have%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%2020%20and%20he%20was%2025%20%E2%80%94%20we%20were%20very%20young%20and%20wanted%20to%20experience%20the%20world%20and%20get%20our%20finances%20together%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeldon%20is%20now%20a%20software%20engineer.%20After%20college%2C%20I%20went%20into%20marketing%20roles%2C%20but%20in%202020%2C%20I%20became%20a%20data%20analyst%20for%20a%20Washington-based%20energy%20company.%20In%202021%2C%20I%20started%20earning%20over%20%24100%2C000%20a%20year.%20We%20were%20tech%20DINKs%2C%20which%20stands%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-dinks-winning-childfree-economy-finances-income-vacation-retirement-kids-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edouble%20income%2C%20no%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20do%20want%20kids%20later%20in%20life%2C%20but%20we%20both%20agree%20that%20now's%20not%20the%20right%20time%20for%20us.%20With%20two%20incomes%20and%20no%20children%2C%20we've%20been%20able%20to%20buy%20a%20house%2C%20pay%20for%20a%20wedding%2C%20build%20up%20our%20savings%2C%20and%20travel.%20I%20even%20quit%20my%209-to-5%20to%20pursue%20my%20passion%20for%20content%20creation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20been%20a%20spate%20of%20tech%20layoffs.%20These%20factors%20make%20me%20feel%20like%20we've%20made%20the%20right%20decision%20by%20putting%20off%20having%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b667deb7-7867-4655-a07c-e2f8a7233462%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20splurged%20and%20traveled%20a%20lot%20during%20our%20tech%20DINK%20era%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20tech%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdinks-childfree-parents-choice-kids-childless-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDINKs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Keldon%20and%20I%20could%20splurge%20on%20whatever%20we%20wanted%20because%20we%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20discretionary%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20both%20worked%20east%20of%20Seattle%20and%20would%20meet%20up%20after%20work%20to%20eat%20out%20or%20watch%20a%20movie.%20We%20saw%20it%20as%20a%20way%20to%20treat%20ourselves%20because%20we%20worked%20incredibly%20hard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202020%2C%20we%20bought%20a%20two-bedroom%20condo%20for%20around%20%24500%2C000.%20We%20combined%20our%20finances%20and%20got%20pre-approved%20for%20a%20mortgage.%20It%20was%20easier%20to%20afford%20a%20home%20with%20two%20incomes%20because%20we%20could%20split%20the%20downpayment%20equally%20between%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20sharing%20expenses%2C%20so%20it%20felt%20like%20everything%20was%20half%20off%2C%20and%20we%20were%20able%20to%20save%20more.%20We%20both%20built%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemergency%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022%3B%20I%20have%20%2431%2C000%20in%20mine.%20We%20stopped%20putting%20money%20into%20them%20to%20prioritize%20savings%20for%20our%20wedding%20and%20honeymoon%20expenses.%20We%20were%20able%20to%20save%20around%20%2420%2C000%20for%20our%20wedding%20in%20August%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20a%20travel%20fund%20with%20%244%2C000%20in%20it.%20We%20also%20have%20a%20home%20renovation%20fund%2C%20and%20we%20put%20extra%20income%20into%20maxing%20out%20our%20Roth%20IRAs%20and%20investing%20in%20a%20regular%20brokerage%20account.%20Our%20savings%20strategy%20was%20pretty%20disciplined.%20We%20could%20put%20away%20a%20little%20over%20half%20our%20income%20after%20taxes%20into%20financial%20goals%20like%20savings%20and%20investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20dog%2C%20a%20pomeranian%2C%20brings%20a%20lot%20joy%20into%20our%20lives%2C%20but%20he%20was%20expensive.%20He%20cost%20around%20%241%2C700%20when%20we%20bought%20him%20a%20month%20after%20getting%20our%20house%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-dinkwad-double-income-no-kids-dog-tiktok-trend-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emaking%20us%20DINKWADs%3C%2Fa%3E%20(double%20income%2C%20no%20kids%2C%20with%20a%20dog).%20We%20spoil%20him%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20treats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Keldon%20and%20I%20could%20travel%20almost%20every%20other%20month%2C%20even%20after%20I%20quit%20my%20job.%20We%20felt%20we%20had%20the%20financial%20security%20to%20do%20this%20because%20we%20already%20had%20a%20home%20and%20emergency%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20went%20to%20places%20like%20Rome%2C%20Mexico%2C%20and%20Finland.%20Having%20the%20time%20and%20freedom%20to%20experience%20the%20world%20was%20awesome%20since%20we%20didn't%20have%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227edae68e-d7e9-4267-af24-10af903bcdc5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20quit%20my%20tech%20job%20to%20become%20a%20content%20creator%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20making%20TikToks%20about%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsmartest-moves-made-with-money-2024-04%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epersonal%20finance%3C%2Fa%3E%20journey%20in%202022.%20On%20TikTok%2C%20people%20told%20me%20I%20was%20making%20an%20impact%20by%20teaching%20them%20new%20things%20about%20finance.%20I%20made%20%2440%2C000%20in%20revenue%20from%20content%20creation%20in%202022%20and%20%24107%2C000%20in%202023%20before%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20my%20income%20from%20content%20creation%20in%202023%20came%20from%20UGC%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-money-from-ugc-user-generated-content-ads%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3