0goes%20toward%20the%20principal%20vs.%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E30-Year%20Fixed%20Mortgage%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20week's%20average%2030-year%20fixed%20mortgage%20rate%20was%207.22%25%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freddiemac.com%2Fpmms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFreddie%20Mac%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20a%20five-basis-point%20increase%20from%20the%20previous%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%20is%20the%20most%20common%20type%20of%20home%20loan.%20With%20this%20type%20of%20mortgage%2C%20you'll%20pay%20back%20what%20you%20borrowed%20over%2030%20years%2C%20and%20your%20interest%20rate%20won't%20change%20for%20the%20life%20of%20the%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lengthy%2030-year%20term%20allows%20you%20to%20spread%20out%20your%20payments%20over%20a%20long%20period%20of%20time%2C%20meaning%20you%20can%20keep%20your%20monthly%20payments%20lower%20and%20more%20manageable.%20The%20trade-off%20is%20that%20you'll%20have%20a%20higher%20rate%20than%20you%20would%20with%20shorter%20terms%20or%20adjustable%20rates.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E15-Year%20Fixed%20Mortgage%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAverage%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2F15-year-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3E15-year%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20inched%20up%20to%206.47%25%20this%20week%2C%20according%20to%20Freddie%20Mac%20data.%20This%20is%20a%20three-point%20increase%20since%20the%20week%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20the%20predictability%20that%20comes%20with%20a%20fixed%20rate%20but%20are%20looking%20to%20spend%20less%20on%20interest%20over%20the%20life%20of%20your%20loan%2C%20a%2015-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%20might%20be%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20you.%20Because%20these%20terms%20are%20shorter%20and%20have%20lower%20rates%20than%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgages%2C%20you%20could%20potentially%20save%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20interest.%20However%2C%20you'll%20have%20a%20higher%20monthly%20payment%20than%20you%20would%20with%20a%20longer%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20Do%20Fed%20Rate%20Hikes%20Affect%20Mortgages%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve%20has%20increased%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-the-federal-funds-rate%5C%22%3Efederal%20funds%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20dramatically%20to%20try%20to%20slow%20economic%20growth%20and%20get%20inflation%20under%20control.%20So%20far%2C%20inflation%20has%20slowed%20significantly%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20a%20bit%20above%20the%20Fed's%202%25%20target%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20aren't%20directly%20impacted%20by%20changes%20to%20the%20federal%20funds%20rate%2C%20but%20they%20often%20trend%20up%20or%20down%20ahead%20of%20Fed%20policy%20moves.%20This%20is%20because%20mortgage%20rates%20change%20based%20on%20investor%20demand%20for%20mortgage-backed%20securities%2C%20and%20this%20demand%20is%20often%20impacted%20by%20how%20investors%20expect%20Fed%20hikes%20to%20affect%20the%20broader%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20has%20indicated%20that%20it's%20likely%20done%20hiking%20rates%20and%20that%20it%20could%20start%20cutting%20this%20year.%20This%20would%20allow%20mortgage%20rates%20to%20trend%20down%20later%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhen%20Will%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Go%20Down%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20increased%20dramatically%20over%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20but%20they're%20expected%20to%20go%20down%20at%20some%20point%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202024%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-cpi-food-energy-gas-prices-consumer-price-index-2024-4%5C%22%3EConsumer%20Price%20Index%20rose%203.5%25%20year-over-year%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Inflation%20has%20slowed%20significantly%20since%20it%20peaked%20last%20year%2C%20but%20it%20has%20to%20slow%20further%20before%20rates%20will%20begin%20to%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C