f%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffiles.pitchbook.com%2Fwebsite%2Ffiles%2Fpdf%2FQ1_2024_PitchBook_Analyst_Note_The_State_of_Private_Market_ESG_and_Impact_Investing_in_2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equieting%20down%20on%20ESG%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20part%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bgreenhushing%26quot%3B%20trend.%20Some%20companies%20that%20made%20a%20big%20deal%20about%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdei-programs-america-diversity-equity-inclusion-pushback-how-to-fix-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDEI%20efforts%20in%202020%20are%20downsizing%20those%2C%20too%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Data%20provided%20to%20me%20by%20FactSet%2C%20a%20financial-data%20company%2C%20shows%20that%20mentions%20of%20ESG%20and%20DEI%20in%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20companies'%20quarterly%20earnings%20calls%20with%20analysts%20have%20taken%20a%20nosedive%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years.%20For%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20of%202020%2C%20131%20companies%20mentioned%20ESG%2C%20and%2034%20mentioned%20DEI%20or%20diversity%20and%20inclusion.%20For%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20of%202023%2C%20those%20numbers%20dropped%20to%2028%20and%20four.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22breakout-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FT6Wls%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Mentions%20of%20ESG%2C%20DEI%2C%20and%20diversity%20and%20inclusion%20in%20S%26amp%3Bamp%3BP%20500%20earnings%20calls%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22478%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20backlash%20has%20certainly%20driven%20the%20quieting%2C%20in%20some%20cases%20companies%20are%20talking%20less%20about%20their%20social%20commitments%20because%20they%20got%20out%20over%20their%20skis%20on%20their%20pledges.%20Companies%20such%20as%20AIG%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20ExxonMobil%20have%20scaled%20back%20some%20of%20their%20climate%20initiatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20saw%20a%20lot%20of%20companies%20make%20very%20bold%20commitments%20%E2%80%94%20we're%20going%20to%20be%20net-zero%20emissions%20by%20whatever%20date%2C%202040%2C%202050%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20often%20those%20commitments%20came%20but%20there%20wasn't%20always%20the%20underlying%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlison%20Taylor%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20New%20York%20University's%20Stern%20School%20of%20Business%20who%20wrote%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BHigher%20Ground%3A%20How%20Business%20Can%20Do%20the%20Right%20Thing%20in%20a%20Turbulent%20World%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20me%20that%2C%20in%20her%20view%2C%20corporate%20America's%20about-face%20isn't%20as%20abrupt%20as%20it%20seems.%20C-suites%20have%20become%20more%20Republican%20over%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20and%20in%20loudly%20proclaiming%20to%20be%20do-gooders%2C%20companies%20have%20also%20drawn%20attention%20to%20their%20political%20donations%2C%20which%20often%20don't%20align%20with%20their%20rhetoric.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20issues%20dominating%20political%20and%20social%20discussions%20are%20much%20thornier%20than%20they%20were%20in%20the%20recent%20past%20%E2%80%94%20speaking%20out%20against%20white%20supremacists%20in%20Charlottesville%20is%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20gimme%2C%20weighing%20in%20on%20the%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict%20is%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20what%20we've%20got%20is%20the%20end%20of%20Roe%20v.%20Wade%2C%20and%20we've%20got%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20and%20we've%20got%20issues%20where%20they're%20much%2C%20much%20more%20divisive%20and%20difficult%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaylor%2C%20a%20longtime%20skeptic%20of%20CEO%20activism%2C%20isn't%20surprised%20the%20friendly-corporation-next-door%20schtick%20has%20gone%20awry%2C%20but%20it%20has%20clearly%20caught%20some%20employees%20unawares.%20Some%20corporations%20have%20encouraged%20the%20creation%20of%20employee%20resource%20groups%2C%20which%20organize%20people%20by%20social%20identities%20and%20beliefs%20and%20in%20some%20cases%20embolden%20them%20to%20push%20for%20change.%20Google%20workers%20have%20previously%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhundreds-google-workers-walk-out-zurich-protest-over-layoffs-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparticipated%20in%20walkouts%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblack-employees-unhappy-with-googles-response-to-protests-2020-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprotests%20and%20kept%20their%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Many%20were%20bewildered%20to%20find%20that%20this%20time%20around%2C%20the%20company%20was%20no%20longer%20having%20it.%20Instead%2C%20it's%20firing%20those%20protesting%20and%20reminding%20everyone%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20company%20is%20not%20a%20democracy%2C%20and%20so%20all%20these%20leaders%20wanted%20to%20imply%20it%20was%20a%20democracy%20when%20it%20suited%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20said.%20%26quot%3BNow%20it%20doesn't%20suit%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20whether%20this%20trend%20of%20companies%20trying%20to%20stick%20to%20straight%20business%20is%20a%20blip%20or%20a%20more%20permanent%20reversal.%20Bud%20Light%20and%20its%20parent%20company%2C%20Anheuser-Busch%2C%20have%20generally%20steered%20clear%20of%20anything%20that%20might%20be%20read%20as%20controversial%20since%20the%20Dylan%20Mulvaney%20debacle%3B%20their%20main%20message%20since%20then%20has%20been%20%26quot%3BWe%20love%20America.%26quot%3B%20Target%20told%20me%20it%20didn't%20have%20anything%20to%20share%20on%20its%202024%20Pride%20plans%20yet%2C%20but%20it%20has%20publicly%20acknowledged%20it's%20likely%20to%20make%20some%20modifications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20people%20I%20spoke%20to%20for%20this%20story%20described%20executives%20as%20more%20on%20edge%20because%20of%20the%20election%20this%20year%3B%20come%202025%2C%20that%20may%20ease.%20The%20anti-woke%20crowd%20is%20extra%20fired%20up%20about%20certain%20issues%20right%20now%2C%20but%20that%20may%20not%20last%20%E2%80%94%20attention%20spans%20are%20short%2C%20and%20hot-button%20issues%20are%20constantly%20changing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20companies'%20backing%20down%20on%20sustainability%20and%20diversity%20efforts%2C%20even%20temporarily%2C%20could%20prove%20short-sighted.%20Sure%2C%20you%20saved%20yourself%20a%20headache%20now%2C%20but%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20setting%20up%20a%20business%20to%20weather%20the%20climate%20crisis%20is%20a%20good%20bet.%20So%20is%20hiring%20diverse%20workers%20and%20appealing%20to%20new%20demographics.%20Despite%20the%20controversy%20last%20year%2C%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20Bud%20Light's%20campaign%20was%20an%20understandable%20business%20decision%3A%20It%20wants%20to%20appeal%20to%20a%20younger%2C%20more%20diverse%20consumer%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnderlying%20this%20all%20is%20one%20central%20question%3A%20Just%20how%20%26quot%3Bwoke%26quot%3B%20are%20companies%20anyway%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommitments%20to%20social%20responsibility%20are%20never%20far-reaching%2C%20said%20Kenneth%20Pucker%2C%20a%20former%20Timberland%20chief%20operating%20officer%20and%20current%20professor%20of%20practice%20at%20the%20Fletcher%20School%20at%20Tufts%20University.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20always%20on%20the%20margins%20because%20the%20main%20goal%20of%20executives%20%E2%80%94%20the%20real%20responsibility%2C%20the%20way%20the%20structure%20of%20the%20system%20is%20organized%2C%20the%20way%20incentives%20work%2C%20the%20way%20the%20rules%20govern%20%E2%80%94%20is%20money%20making.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20may%20be%20a%20great%20un-wokening%2C%20but%20maybe%20corporate%20America%20was%20actually%20never%20that%20committed%20to%20the%20idea%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%