p%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20proposal%2C%20gig%20workers%20would%20be%20paid%20an%20hourly%20rate%20of%20%2419.97%20for%20their%20time%20spent%20retrieving%20and%20delivering%20orders.%20While%20that%20seems%20consistent%20with%20Seattle's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheres-how-much-retail-jobs-pay-from-amazon-to-walmart-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eminimum%20wage%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20employees%2C%20the%20gig%20workers%20covered%20by%20the%20PayUp%20law%20are%20only%20paid%20for%20%26quot%3Bactive%20time%26quot%3B%20spent%20working%20on%20orders%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20that%20time%20spent%20trying%20to%20claim%20an%20order%20is%20uncompensated.%20They're%20also%20responsible%20for%20their%20own%20costs%2C%20such%20as%20gas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20aspects%20of%20the%20job%20had%20led%20Seattle's%20city%20council%20to%20create%20a%20system%20that%20pays%20workers%20based%20on%20the%20miles%20they%20drive%20and%20the%20minutes%20they%20spend%20on%20the%20job.%20PayUp%20also%20demands%20that%20no%20offer%20pays%20less%20than%20%245.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20proposal%20would%20do%20away%20with%20that%20%245%20minimum%20and%20the%20per-minute%20payment.%20Instead%2C%20gig%20workers%20would%20get%20paid%2035%20cents%20per%20mile%20%E2%80%94%20down%20from%20the%20current%2074%20cents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20also%20eliminate%20or%20cut%20back%20other%20protections%20for%20gig%20workers%20in%20the%20city.%20For%20example%2C%20a%20PayUp%20rule%20giving%20workers%20two%20minutes%20to%20review%20an%20order%20before%20accepting%20it%20would%20shrink%20to%2045%20seconds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20is%20scheduled%20for%20a%20committee%20vote%20on%20Thursday.%20If%20it%20passes%2C%20the%20proposal%20could%20face%20a%20vote%20by%20the%20full%20Council%20on%20May%2021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d26f947e-c756-43ba-8111-91649a5d7b7a%5C%22%3E'That%20makes%20a%20difference'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that%20vote%20passes%2C%20the%20bill%20will%20result%20in%20a%20significant%20pay%20cut%20for%20gig%20workers%2C%20according%20to%20estimates%20released%20Monday%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.workingwa.org%2Ffor-media%2F2024%2F5%2F6%2Fnelson-proposal-would-cut-gig-worker-pay-to-1317hour-more-than-6-below-seattles-minimum-wage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorking%20Washington%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20group%20that%20advocated%20for%20PayUp.%20For%20example%2C%20a%20gig%20worker%20who%20spent%20five%20hours%20of%20active%20time%20and%20drove%2032%20miles%20would%20make%20%2415.81%20an%20hour%20%E2%80%94%20below%20the%20city's%20minimum%20wage%20%E2%80%94%20after%20accounting%20for%20expenses%2C%20they%20calculated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHourly%20pay%20would%20be%20even%20lower%20%E2%80%94%20%2413.17%20%E2%80%94%20after%20accounting%20for%20the%20time%20that%20a%20gig%20worker%20would%20likely%20spend%20on%20the%20apps%20just%20to%20find%20and%20claim%20orders%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJustin%20Taylor%2C%20who%20has%20delivered%20and%20driven%20for%20multiple%20apps%20in%20Seattle%20over%20the%20last%20four%20years%2C%20said%20his%20pay%20has%20increased%20by%20%24100%20a%20week%20on%20average%20since%20PayUp%20went%20into%20effect%20%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20he's%20delivering%20fewer%20orders%20than%20he%20did%20before%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20makes%20a%20difference%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIt%20allowed%20me%20to%20do%20things%20like%20install%20new%20front%20brakes%20on%20my%20car.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20proposal%20before%20Seattle's%20City%20Council%20becomes%20law%2C%20Taylor%20said%2C%20he'll%20once%20again%20be%20reliant%20on%20customers'%20tips%20to%20cover%20his%20expenses%20and%20make%20money%20working%20for%20services%20like%20DoorDash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20delivery%20companies%20have%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20they%20oppose%20the%20changes%20that%20took%20effect%20in%20January.%20In%20emails%20and%20calls%20to%20action%20sent%20to%20gig%20workers%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstacart-doordash-pushing-back-against-seattle-gig-worker-laws-payup-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDoorDash%2C%20Instacart%2C%20Uber%2C%20and%20others%20have%20claimed%20that%20there%20are%20fewer%20orders%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20gig%20workers%20to%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstacart-adding-miles-to-seattle-deliveries-gig-work-pay-law-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshoppers%20for%20Instacart%20have%20also%20had%20to%20drive%20miles%3C%2Fa%3E%20out%20of%20their%20way%20to%20deliver%20orders%20in%20Seattle's%20suburbs%20as%20the%20company%20routed%20them%20to%20stores%20outside%20city%20limits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeattle%20City%20Council%20President%20Nelson%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20an%20interview%20from%20Business%20Insider.%20In%20a%20hearing%20on%20the%20bill%20on%20April%2025%2C%20Nelson%20said%20that%20she%20had%20worked%20with%20some%20of%20the%20delivery%20companies%20as%20well%20as%20Drive%20Forward%2C%20a%20group%20whose%20leadership%20includes%20multiple%20current%20and%20former%20employees%20for%20Uber%20and%20DoorDash%2C%20to%20draft%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20people%20realize%20this%20was%20an%20agreement%20that%20was%20forged%20between%20Drive%20Forward%20and%20the%20network%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20the%20Council.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20DoorDash%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%3A%20%26quot%3BPredictably%2C%20Working%20Washington's%20opposition%20to%20this%20proposal%20is%20not%20rooted%20in%20reality.%20The%20proposed%20law%20guarantees%20Dashers%20will%20earn%20nearly%20%2420%20per%20hour%20on%20delivery%20in%20addition%20to%20mileage%20and%20tips.%20We're%20grateful%20that%20Council%20President%20Nelson%20and%20Drive%20Forward%20were%20able%20to%20reconvene%20stakeholders%20and%20reach%20a%20compromise%20that%20better%20serves%20Dashers%2C%20local%20businesses%2C%20and%20consumers%20in%20Seattle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Instacart%20said%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bsupports%20the%20pragmatic%20approach%20being%20taken%20by%20the%20new%20Seattle%20City%20Council%20as%20they%20balance%20the%20needs%20of%20workers%2C%20customers%2C%20and%20businesses%20across%20the%20city%20and%20reform%20the%20current%20version%20of%20PayUp%20legislation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUber%20supports%20the%20complete%20package%2C%20and%20believes%20it%20will%20go%20a%20long%20way%20to%20ease%20the%20operational%20burdens%20and%20costs%20experienced%20by%20customers%20throughout%20Seattle%20and%20reduce%20delivery%20times%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20gig%20worker%20Taylor%20said%20he%20was%20dismayed%20that%20the%20delivery%20companies%20have%20had%20such%20a%20direct%20role%20in%20developing%20the%20bill%20that%20would%20replace%20PayUp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20me%2C%20it's%20basically%20saying%20we're%20allowing%20lobbyists%20to%20write%20our%20laws%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20deliver%20food%2C%20groceries%2C%20or%20other%20items%20as%20a%20gig%20worker%20and%20have%20a%20story%20idea%20to%20share%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aabitter%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eabitter%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fseattle-gig-workers-could-get-pay-cut-under-payup-replacement-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715247061000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663b8fb4f27898f532d4ffd3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsi