ttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fxi-jinping-in-paris-to-meet-emmanuel-macron-with-trade-ukraine-talks-planned-5599718%5C%22%3EIn%20France%2C%20there%20was%20nothing%20that%20Xi%3C%2Fa%3E%20offered%20to%20try%20to%20change%20the%20antagonistic%20posturing.%20He%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20China%20opposes%20%26quot%3Busing%20the%20Ukraine%20crisis%20to%20cast%20blame%2C%20smear%20a%20third%20country%20and%20incite%20a%20new%20Cold%20War%26quot%3B%2C%20while%20announcing%20that%20he%20supported%20the%20French%20president's%20call%20for%20an%20%26quot%3BOlympics%20truce%26quot%3B.%20Beijing%20recognises%20well%20that%20this%20is%20an%20exercise%20in%20futility%20and%20wishful%20thinking%20on%20the%20part%20of%20Paris%2C%20so%20it%20finds%20no%20harm%20in%20mentioning%20aspects%20of%20policy%2C%20if%20only%20to%20massage%20France's%20ego.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20both%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Femmanuel-macron%5C%22%3EFrench%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20German%20Chancellor%20Olaf%20Scholz%20trying%20to%20endear%20themselves%20to%20Beijing%2C%20the%20divisions%20within%20the%20European%20Union%20on%20China%20stand%20out%20starkly.%20This%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20there%20has%20been%20a%20dramatic%20change%20in%20perceptions%20about%20China%20in%20Europe.%20What%20was%20once%20considered%20a%20binding%20factor%20-%20trade%20-%20has%20today%20emerged%20as%20a%20major%20bone%20of%20contention.%20Both%20Europe%20and%20China%20have%20invested%20heavily%20in%20each%20other's%20markets%2C%20but%20barriers%20to%20market%20access%20and%20investment%20restrictions%20persist.%20Europe%20has%20expressed%20concerns%20about%20fair%20competition%2C%20state%20subsidies%2C%20and%20the%20protection%20of%20intellectual%20property%20rights%20in%20China%2C%20while%20China%20seeks%20greater%20access%20to%20European%20markets%20and%20technology%20transfer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EChinese%20Investments%20Are%20Important%20For%20Some%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEuropean%20countries%20have%20criticised%20China%20for%20its%20lack%20of%20reciprocity%20in%20trade%20and%20investment%20relations.%20While%20European%20markets%20are%20relatively%20open%20to%20Chinese%20investment%2C%20access%20to%20the%20Chinese%20market%20remains%20restricted%20for%20European%20companies%2C%20with%20concerns%20about%20unfair%20competition%20and%20forced%20technology%20transfer.%20Europe%20is%20wary%20of%20China's%20growing%20technological%20capabilities%20and%20its%20potential%20implications%20for%20cybersecurity.%20Concerns%20about%20Chinese%20telecommunications%20companies%20such%20as%20Huawei%20and%20their%20involvement%20in%20critical%20infrastructure%20projects%20have%20led%20some%20European%20countries%20to%20restrict%20or%20exclude%20them%20from%20their%20networks%20due%20to%20perceived%20security%20risks%20and%20potential%20espionage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20parts%20of%20Europe%20continue%20with%20their%20outreach%20to%20China.%20Serbia's%20ties%20with%20China%20have%20accelerated%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20though%20it%20continues%20to%20seek%20an%20entry%20into%20the%20European%20Union.%20Last%20year%2C%20the%20two%20nations%20inked%20a%20free%20trade%20pact%2C%20bolstering%20their%20%26quot%3Bcomprehensive%20strategic%20partnership%26quot%3B%20established%20in%202016%20during%20Xi's%20prior%20visit%20to%20Serbia.%20Following%20Belgrade%2C%20China's%20president%20will%20head%20to%20Budapest%2C%20where%20Hungarian%20Prime%20Minister%20Viktor%20Orban%20has%20emerged%20as%20Xi's%20staunchest%20ally%20among%20EU%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChinese%20investments%20play%20a%20significant%20role%20there%20as%20well%2C%20with%20projects%20like%20the%20electric%20car%20giant%20BYD's%20factory%20allowing%20Orban%20to%20challenge%20the%20EU%20consensus%20on%20issues%20over%20a%20range%20of%20subjects.%20The%20Hungarian%20government%20has%20tried%20its%20best%20to%20sweeten%20the%20deal%20for%20Chinese%20investments%2C%20and%20a%20high-speed%20railway%20seeking%20to%20connect%20Central%20Europe%20to%20the%20ports%20of%20Thessaloniki%20and%20Piraeus%20is%20a%20case%20in%20point.%20Xi's%20visits%20to%20Serbia%20and%20Hungary%20this%20week%20also%20underscore%20the%20enthusiasm%20for%20China%20in%20certain%20parts%20of%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompeting%20Interests%20And%20Values%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20divisions%20within%20Europe%20over%20China%20are%20only%20going%20to%20grow%20in%20sync%20with%20a%20spectrum%20of%20interests%20and%20concerns%20among%20its%20member%20states.%20While%20some%20nations%20prioritise%20economic%20cooperation%20and%20view%20China%20as%20a%20crucial%20trading%20partner%20and%20source%20of%20investment%2C%20others%20are%20becoming%20more%20apprehensive%20about%20Beijing's%20growing%20influence%2C%20particularly%20regarding%20human%20rights%2C%20disinformation%2C%20and%20geopolitical%20ambitions.%20Additionally%2C%20debates%20over%20infrastructure%20and%20connectivity%2C%20technology%20standards%2C%205G%20networks%2C%20and%20supply%20chain%20security%20further%20underscore%20the%20discord.%20These%20divisions%20within%20Europe%20illustrate%20the%20complexities%20of%20navigating%20relations%20with%20China%20amidst%20competing%20interests%20and%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20geopolitical%20tensions%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%20become%20starker%2C%20Europe's%20space%20to%20manoeuvre%20will%20only%20shrink%20and%20the%20ability%20of%20Beijing%20to%20exploit%20the%20cleavages%20within%20the%20West%20will%20also%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20New%20Delhi%2C%20Europe%20has%20emerged%20as%20an%20important%20partner%20sharing%20convergent%20geopolitical%20worldviews.%20A%20strong%20united%20European%20voice%20in%20the%20global%20order%20is%20important%20for%20managing%20the%20turbulence%20in%20the%20balance%20of%20power.%20India%20would%20be%20hoping%20that%20the%20divisions%20within