%3EWhat's%20the%20company%20culture%20like%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20thing%20I%20tell%20people%20to%20ask%20is%20about%20company%20culture.%20That's%20a%20big%20one.%20It's%20such%20a%20make-it-or-break-it%20for%20enjoying%20your%20job.%20I%20wanted%20my%20audience%20to%20know%20that%20asking%20about%20it%20is%20so%20important%20because%20if%20you're%20miserable%20in%20your%20job%2C%20you're%20only%20setting%20yourself%20up%20to%20fail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ea69e943-0de5-44d4-a3b6-1b8e06b334f5%5C%22%3EWhat's%20the%20lowdown%20on%20my%20predecessor%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20one%20is%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20did%20the%20person%20who%20held%20this%20role%20before%20me%20do%20that%20was%20appreciated%20but%20not%20required%20based%20on%20the%20job%20description%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20suggest%20this%20one%20because%20I%20want%20my%20audience%20to%20put%20themselves%20in%20the%20role%20already.%20It's%20an%20assumptive%20selling%20tactic.%20I%20always%20say%20go%20into%20the%20interview%20and%20sell%20yourself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20that%20question%20one%20time%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%26quot%3BWhat%20are%20you%20going%20to%20miss%20most%20about%20this%20person%3F%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20interviewer%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20they%20got%20Starbucks%20all%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%20And%20I%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BGreat%2C%20I%20guess%20we'll%20be%20getting%20Starbucks%20for%20the%20office%20all%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222cfb523e-292b-421f-9dde-bc902d5ed684%5C%22%3EWhat%20do%20my%20colleagues%20require%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20question%20was%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20can%20I%20best%20suit%20the%20needs%20of%20my%20direct%20counterparts%3F%26quot%3B%20That%20came%20from%20wanting%20to%20understand%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0in%20the%20most%20professional%20way%20%E2%80%94%20the%20team%20you're%20walking%20into.%20It%20helps%20me%20understand%20and%20identify%20how%20I%20would%20fit%20into%20the%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20seen%20teams%20before%20where%20they%20just%20don't%20get%20along.%20But%20you%20don't%20know%20that%20until%20you%20sit%20down%20on%20the%20first%20day.%20And%20at%20that%20point%2C%20it's%20already%20too%20late.%20You're%20either%20leaving%2C%20or%20you've%20got%20to%20deal%20with%20this%20until%20you%20can%20figure%20out%20another%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2285c54d92-7a2b-4785-9b78-1da371b0d5b6%5C%22%3EHow%20successful%20is%20the%20team%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENo.%204%20is%20what%20the%20current%20state%20of%20the%20department%20is%20in%20reference%20to%20the%20bottom%20line.%20That%20has%20to%20do%20with%20asking%20about%20sales%2C%20of%20course%2C%20but%20I'm%20also%20asking%3A%20%26quot%3BAm%20I%20walking%20into%20a%20failing%20department%3F%20Are%20you%20expecting%20me%20to%20turn%20things%20around%3F%20Are%20you%20expecting%20me%20to%20just%20take%20the%20blame%20for%20something%20that's%20already%20failing%3F%20Or%20are%20you%20guys%20seeing%20numbers%20you've%20never%20seen%20before%20and%20need%20more%20people%3F%26quot%3B%20And%2C%20if%20so%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20did%20you%20do%20to%20see%20those%20numbers%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ef1d37dd-6f1f-407a-9961-a11c83333ed9%5C%22%3EWhat%20does%20the%20company's%20future%20look%20like%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20fifth%20question%20is%20my%20favorite.%20It's%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20the%20company's%20three-year%2C%20five-year%2C%20and%2010-year%20plan%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20love%20this%20one%20because%20I've%20never%20walked%20into%20a%20job%20and%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20only%20going%20to%20be%20here%20for%20one%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BI'm%20only%20doing%20this%20to%20collect%20a%20paycheck.%26quot%3B%20I%20always%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BThink%20like%20the%20CEO.%26quot%3B%20I%20never%20want%20to%20go%20into%20a%20job%20and%20strive%20to%20just%20be%20an%20associate.%20That's%20just%20where%20you%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20you%20really%20need%