5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20standing%20in%20the%20shadow%20of%20a%20giant%20chess%20piece%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66393035ec0c696569017af3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221067%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ENicol%C3%A1s%20Ortega%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20singular%20misery%20to%20trying%20your%20very%20best%2C%20after%20months%20of%20training%2C%20only%20to%20be%20crushed%20by%20a%206-year-old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20December%2C%20I%20spent%20a%20cloudy%20day%20holed%20up%20at%20the%20Mechanics'%20Institute%2C%20a%20venerable%20chess%20club%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20to%20play%20in%20the%2022nd%20annual%20McClain%20Memorial%20Tournament.%20It%20was%20my%20first%20in-person%20chess%20competition%2C%20and%20I%20was%20full%20of%20optimism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20faced%20a%20severe-looking%20child%20who%20wore%20a%20food-stained%20sweatshirt%20emblazoned%20with%20a%20cartoon%20penguin.%20He%20did%20not%20speak.%20He%20alternated%20between%20fidgeting%20uncontrollably%20and%20fixing%20me%20with%20a%20disconcerting%20death%20stare.%20He%20spent%20much%20of%20his%20time%20between%20moves%20crawling%20around%20beneath%20the%20table%20(an%20interesting%20psych-out%20technique%2C%20but%20not%20one%20I%20think%20I%20could%20pull%20off).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20in%20the%20game%2C%20I%20made%20an%20amateur%20mistake%20that%20left%20me%20down%20a%20knight.%20From%20there%20it%20was%20all%20over%2C%20even%20if%20I%20didn't%20immediately%20realize%20it.%20A%20checkmate%20soon%20followed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20game%20had%20been%20against%20a%20middle-aged%20asset%20manager%2C%20and%20we'd%20discussed%20the%20strangeness%20of%20us%20adults%20competing%20against%20children.%20(He%20also%20beat%20me.)%20After%20an%20undignified%20lunch%20of%20Doritos%20and%20a%20chocolate%20protein%20shake%2C%20I%20managed%20to%20eke%20out%20a%20win%20against%20my%20third%20opponent.%20A%20tech%20worker%20in%20her%20mid-20s%2C%20she%20noted%20she%20was%20nursing%20a%20severe%20hangover%2C%20and%20she%20had%20a%20helpful%20habit%20of%20involuntarily%20gasping%20whenever%20she%20realized%20she'd%20made%20a%20mistake.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20I'd%20take%20whatever%20modicum%20of%20dignity%20I%20could%20salvage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20three%20decades%20of%20my%20life%2C%20I'd%20had%20fleeting%20phases%20of%20mild%20interest%20in%20chess%2C%20playing%20the%20occasional%20game%20online%20while%20procrastinating%20or%20over%20the%20board%20with%20a%20drink.%20But%20the%20game's%20foreboding%20density%20and%20association%20with%20supreme%20intellect%20dissuaded%20me%20from%20going%20any%20deeper.%20Over%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20however%2C%20a%20drumbeat%20of%20fanfare%20and%20tabloid%20headlines%20about%20the%20seemingly%20staid%20game%20became%20inescapable.%20Like%20so%20many%20other%20people%2C%20I%20got%20chess-pilled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChess.com%2C%20the%20world's%20leading%20chess%20site%2C%20now%20regularly%20reports%20record%20numbers%20of%20players%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0it%20said%20that%20in%20February%202023%20it%20hostedhosting%20more%20than%201%20billion%20games%20a%20month%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0sporadically%20crashing%20under%20the%20weight%20of%20demand.%20The%20pandemic's%20enforced%20isolation%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-netflix-is-changing-the-entertainment-industry-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENetflix's%3C%2Fa%3E%20smash%20hit%20%26quot%3BThe%20Queen's%20Gambit%26quot%3B%20collectively%20introduced%20an%20entire%20generation%20to%20the%20game.%20Socialites%20are%20playing%20chess%20on%20%26quot%3BThe%20Real%20Housewives%20of%20New%20York%20City.%26quot%3B%20Twitch%20streamers%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-started-with-youtube-podcasts-build-an-audience-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYouTubers%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20racked%20up%20millions%20of%20followers%20and%20ushered%20in%20a%20radical%20new%20culture%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0meme-drenched%2C%20rapid-fire%2C%20and%20drama-prone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChess%20has%20never%20been%20more%20popular%2C%20but%20its%20ugly%20side%20has%20also%20never%20been%20more%20exposed.%20The%20same%20characteristics%20that%20have%20driven%20its%20popularity%20online%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0an%20easy-to-understand%20eight-by-eight%20grid%2C%20a%20strategy%20without%20chance%20or%20luck%20%E2%80%94%20have%20also%20made%20it%20a%20cheater's%20paradise.%20Meanwhile%2C%20rampant%20sexism%20festers%20at%20chess'%20heart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20the%20hell%20was%20happening%20to%20the%20game%20of%20kings%3F%20To%20find%20out%2C%20I%20decided%20I%20needed%20to%20get%20better%20at%20the%20game%20and%20face%20off%20against%20everyone%20I%20talked%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201990%2C%20when%20Judit%20Polg%C3%A1r%2C%20the%20greatest%20female%20chess%20player%2C%20was%20emerging%20as%20a%20child%20prodigy%2C%20the%20world%20champion%20Gary%20Kasparov%20dismissed%20her%20as%20%26quot%3Bafter%20all%2C%20a%20woman.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20all%20comes%20down%20to%20the%20imperfections%20of%20the%20feminine%20psyche%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BNo%20woman%20can%20sustain%20a%20prolonged%20battle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESexism%20persists%20in%20every%20level%20of%20the%20game.%20In%201990%2C%20according%20to%20the%20US%20Chess%20Federation%2C%20only%204%25%20of%20chess%20players%20were%20women.%20Today%20it's%2014%25.%20There%20are%20innumerable%20tales%20of%20how%20women%20were%20belittled%2C%20mistreated%2C%20harassed%2C%20and%20abused%20%E2%80%94%20from%20snide%20remarks%20about%20%26quot%3Blosing%20to%20a%20girl%26quot%3B%20at%20a%20chess%20club%20to%20sexist%20comments%20during%20online%20play.%20Juliana%20Gallin%2C%20a%20graphic%20designer%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20told%20me%20before%20a%20game%20on%20Chess.com%20(she%20wiped%20the%20floor%20with%20me)%20that%20she%20had%20deliberately%20omitted%20any%20references%20to%20her%20gender%20in%20her%20online%20profile.%20Even%20at%20professional%20tournaments%2C%20many%20women%20say%20commentators%20and%20audiences%20sometimes%20fixate%20on%20their%20appearances%20and%20clothes%20rather%20than%20the%20quality%20of%20their%20chess.%20FIDE%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fethics.fide.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2FNew-EDC-Procedural-Rules-as-approved-by-FIDE-Council.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einternational%20chess%20body%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20requires%20anyone%20wishing%20to%20make%20a%20misconduct%20complaint%20to%20first%20pay%20a%20fee%20of%2075%20euros.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20the%20chess%20world%20had%20its%20own%20%23MeToo%20moment.%20It%20started%20when%20the%20grandmaster%20Jennifer%20Shahade%20accused%20Alejandro%20Ram%C3%ADrez%2C%20a%20grandmaster%20and%20well-connected%20coach%2C%20of%20sexual%20assault.%20A%20slew%20of%20further%20allegations%20against%20Ram%C3%ADrez%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20claims%20that%20the%20US%20Chess%20Federation%20had%20failed%20to%20act%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Falejandro-ramirez-jennifer-shahade-chess-allegations-622263b8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esoon%20followed%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(Ram%C3%ADrez%20has%20denied%20the%20allegations.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShahade%20and%20I%20played%20a%20quick%20game%20%E2%80%94%20she%20smothered%20me%2C%20picking%20off%20my%20pawns%20until%20my%20structure%20crumbled%20%E2%80%94%20and%20talked.%20Shahade%20told%20me%20that%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20gender%20imbalance%2C%20part%20of%20the%20issue%20is%20that%20chess%20is%20%26quot%3Bcomplex%20to%20attack%20because%20there's%20so%20many%20different%20cultures%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bevery%20country%20might%20have%20its%20own%20policy%20for%20safe%20play.%26quot%3B%20Beyond%20that%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Ball%20ages%20play%20together%20%E2%80%94%20which%20mostly%20is%20a%20really%20awesome%20thing%20about%20the%20game%20that%20we%20love%20%E2%80%94%20but%20unfortunately%20for%20bad%20actors%20that%20could%20be%20an%20opportunity%20for%20grooming.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20there's%20no%20easier%20place%20for%20bad%20actors%20to%20take%20root%20than%20in%20chess'%20most%20popular%20venue%3A%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20anything%20else%2C%20the%20internet%20has%20transformed%20how%20chess%20is%20played%20and%20talked%20about.%20It%20has%20infused%20the%201%2C500-year-old%20game%20with%20modern%20video-game%20sensibilities%20and%20smack%20talk.%20Online%20chess%20can%20feel%20a%20world%20away%20from%20the%20carefully%20considered%20hourslong%20games%20of%20old%3B%20many%20modern%20players%20prefer%20%26quot%3Bbullet%20chess%2C%26quot%3B%20whose%20warp%20speed%20games%20take%20less%20than%20three%20minutes.%20Beyond%20Reddit%20hubs%20like%20the%20more%20pedantic%20r%2FChess%20(1.1%20million%20members)%20and%20the%20oddball%2C%20shitposting%20r%2FAnarchyChess%20(500%2C000)%2C%20ground%20zero%20for%20chess'%20reimagining%20is%20video%20platforms%20like%20YouTube%20and%20Twitch.%20Dedicated%20chess%20influencers%20like%20Levy%20%26quot%3BGothamChess%26quot%3B%20Rozman%20(nearly%205%20million%20YouTube%20subscribers)%20and%20the%20Botez%20sisters%20(1.5%20million%20subscribers)%20offer%20guidance%20to%20amateurs%20like%20me%2C%20dissecting%20tournament%20games%20and%20diving%20into%20the%20nearly%20constant%20beef%20between%20chess%20celebs.%20Even%20grandmasters%20%E2%80%94%20historically%20cast%20as%20cerebral%20recluses%20%E2%80%94%20are%20getting%20in%20on%20the%20action.%20The%20five-time%20US%20champion%20Hikaru%20Nakamura%20(2.3%20million%20subscribers)%20has%20become%20one%20of%20the%20most%20prolific%20streamers%20out%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rey%20Enigma%20plays%20chess%20against%20Anna%20Cramling%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663972f410dfcda40967518c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERey%20Enigma%20(1.8%20million%20YouTube%20followers)%20plays%20against%20Anna%20Cramling%20(900%2C000%20followers).%3Cp%3EMiguel%20Pereira%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20definitely%20can%20make%20in%20general%20a%20lot%20more%20from%20making%20content%20than%20what%20you%20can%20from%20playing%20competitive%20chess%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Anna%20Cramling%2C%20a%20fast-talking%2021-year-old%20Swedish%20player%20with%20nearly%20900%2C000%20YouTube%20subscribers.%20After%20we%20chatted%2C%20we%20played%20a%20quick%20game%3B%20I%20timed%20out%20with%20no%20good%20moves%20open%20to%20me.%20All%20the%20time%20in%20the%20world%20wouldn't%20have%20made%20a%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20seedier%20side%20of%20internet%20culture%20has%20also%20wormed%20its%20way%20into%20chess.%20%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20downside%20to%20what%20I%20do%20is%20I%20don't%20always%20feel%20safe%2C%26quot%3B%20Cramling%20said.%20Some%20of%20her%20followers%2C%20she%20says%2C%20are%20often%20%26quot%3Btrying%20to%20get%20to%20know%20things%20about%20me.%26quot%3B%20Poor%20sportsmanship%20abounds%3A%20Some%20players%20rage%20quit%20when%20they%20make%20mistakes%2C%20try%20to%20%26quot%3Bstall%26quot%3B%20their%20opponents%2C%20or%20abort%20games%20if%20they%20don't%20get%20to%20play%20as%20white.%20Chat%20rooms%20are%20full%20of%20normalized%20abuse%2C%20often%20sexual%20or%20racist.%20Sometimes%20dark%20behavior%20bleeds%20out%20beyond%20the%20screen%3A%20In%20late%202023%2C%20Nakamura%20said%20the%20police%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkick.com%2Fgmhikaru%3Fclip%3Dclip_01HGP490KWBC8473KX5F71RV06%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eturned%20up%20at%20his%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20someone%20tried%20to%20%26quot%3Bswat%26quot%3B%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20is%20playing%20online%20as%20fulfilling%20as%20playing%20over%20the%20board%3F%20As%20I%20explored%2C%20I%20kept%20up%20a%20steady%20stream%20of%20middling%20games%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FChess.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChess.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20my%20Elo%20rating%20slowly%20rising%20%E2%80%94%20but%20wanted%20a%20more%20immersive%20experience.%20I%20decided%20to%20devote%20an%20entire%20day%20to%20playing%20bullet%20chess.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20version%20I%20played%2C%20a%201%3A1%20time%20control%2C%20each%20player%20was%20allotted%20one%20minute%20total%20for%20the%20entire%20game%20plus%20one%20additional%20second%20per%20move.%20My%20first%20game%20went%20beautifully%3A%20excellent%20piece%20development%2C%20no%20big%20mistakes%2C%20and%20a%20neat%20checkmate.%20During%20game%20two%2C%20I%20started%20to%20feel%20a%20little%20frantic.%20By%20hour%20two%2C%20the%20games%20were%20blurring%20into%20one%20another%20%E2%80%94%20aching%20hands%2C%20no%20time%20for%20strategy%2C%20just%20vibes.%20When%20I%20took%20a%20break%20for%20a%20virtual%20doctor's%20appointment%2C%20I%20was%20seized%20with%20a%20compulsion%20to%20fill%20out%20the%20intake%20forms%20at%20blitzkrieg%20speed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20breakthrough%20when%20I%20switched%20up%20the%20time%20control.%20Now%20I%20was%20playing%20just%20a%20flat%20minute%20per%20player%2C%20no%20additional%20time.%20Suddenly%20I%20was%20winning%20clearly%20lost%20games%20because%20I%20was%20just%20a%20bit%20faster%20on%20the%20draw.%20All%20I%20had%20to%20do%20was%20hide%20my%20king%20in%20the%20corner%20and%20make%20my%20structure%20just%20convoluted%20enough%2C%20and%20I'd%20win%20by%20default%20as%20my%20opponents%20timed%20out.%20It%20was%20a%20lightning-fast%20game%20of%20pattern%20recognition%20and%20counterstrike%20reflexes%2C%20and%20totally%20unconducive%20to%20improving%20my%20actual%20chess%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEight%20hours%20later%2C%20I%20was%20150%20games%20down%20and%20completely%20exhausted.%20It%20was%20time%20to%20log%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOut%20in%20the%20world%2C%20chess'%20resurgence%20has%20been%20accompanied%20by%20a%20wave%20of%20new%20clubs%20and%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Feducation%2F2023%2F04%2F15%2Fschool-chess-class-clubs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20chess%20was%20causing%20an%20%26quot%3Bepidemic%20of%20student%20distraction.%26quot%3B%20In%20Berkeley%2C%20California%2C%20a%20controversial%20unlicensed%20street%20club%20has%20become%20a%20flash%20point%20for%20debates%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.berkeleyside.org%2F2023%2F10%2F06%2Fstudents-community-defend-telegraph-chess-tables-berkeley-city-council%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egentrification%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.berkeleydailyplanet.com%2Fissue%2F2023-10-04%2Farticle%2F50429%3Fheadline%3DThe-City-of-Berkeley-Makes-a-Pawn-of-the-Chess-Club---Steve-Martinot%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epolice%20brutality%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20I%20visited%2C%20I%20was%20bested%20by%20a%20guy%20who%20I%20suspected%20was%20extremely%20high%20and%20who%20got%20up%20to%20dance%20to%20Bill%20Withers%20between%20moves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20couple%20months%20into%20my%20chess%20journey%2C%20I%20was%20in%20New%20York%20City%20for%20the%20week.%20I%20made%20a%20pilgrimage%20to%20the%20Marshall%20Chess%20Club%2C%20a%20109-year-old%20institution%20in%20Greenwich%20Village.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInside%2C%20rows%20of%20players%20sat%20in%20perfect%20silence%20as%20the%20bust%20of%20the%20club's%20founder%2C%20Frank%20Marshall%2C%20the%20American%20chess%20champion%20of%201909%2C%20frowned%20down%20at%20them.%20But%20my%20itch%20to%20play%20could%20not%20be%20scratched%3A%20The%20club%20was%20hosting%20a%20tournament%20that%20day%2C%20a%20nice%20man%20told%20me%20apologetically%2C%20for%20high-ranking%20players%20only.%20Even%20the%20youngest%20attendees%20would%20demolish%20me.%20%26quot%3BThese%20aren't%20your%20normal%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20evening%2C%20I%20went%20to%20an%20East%20Village%20bar%20and%20found%20a%20very%20different%20scene%20at%20Club%20Chess.%20Beneath%20impressionist%20murals%20of%20naked%20women%2C%20and%20among%20candles%20and%20pumping%20EDM%2C%20an%20eclectic%20crowd%20of%20hipsters%2C%20skaters%2C%20and%20the%20occasional%20dyed-in-the-wool%20chess%20nerd%20mingled.%20There%20were%20no%20chess%20clocks%20in%20sight%2C%20and%20downstairs%20there%20was%20a%20full-on%20dance%20floor.%20It%20was%20standing%20room%20only.%20Founded%20in%202023%20by%20Alexander%20Luke%20Bahta%20%E2%80%94%20who%20spent%20the%20evening%20swanning%20around%2C%20tailed%20by%20a%20photographer%20and%20reporter%20for%20a%20lifestyle%20blog%20%E2%80%94%20Club%20Chess%20has%20been%20described%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fsport%2F2023%2Fsep%2F13%2Fnew-york-gen-z-chess-clubs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.curbed.com%2Farticle%2Fclub-chess-maneros-of-mulberry.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20epicenter%20of%20chess'%20ascendance%20in%20nightlife.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20played%20a%20young%20Canadian%20mycologist%20in%20an%20evenly%20matched%20game%20that%20she%20ultimately%20resigned.%20Then%20came%20a%20wiry%20Romanian%20in%20athleisure%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0Elo%20rating%202200%2C%20extremely%20good%20%E2%80%94%20who%20inexorably%20ground%20me%20down%2C%20trapping%20one%20of%20my%20bishops%20and%20stomping%20through%20my%20pawn%20structure.%20Afterward%20I%20watched%20him%20play%20the%20burly%20security%20guard%20and%20checkmate%20him%20barely%20a%20dozen%20moves%20in.%20The%20bouncer%20%26quot%3Bplays%20unconventionally%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Romanian%20said%20diplomatically.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20guy's%20a%20monster%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bouncer%20told%20me%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20work%20looming%20the%20next%20day%2C%20I%20left%20the%20party%2C%20still%20going%20strong%2C%20at%20about%2011%20p.m.%2C%20feeling%20rejuvenated.%20It%20had%20been%20chess%20at%20its%20purest%20and%20most%20freeing%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0no%20scores%20or%20internet%20trash%20talk%20to%20be%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20heard%20anything%20about%20chess%20in%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20it's%20probably%20been%20about%20anal%20beads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20the%20world%20champion%20Magnus%20Carlsen%20accused%20the%20grandmaster%20Hans%20Niemann%2C%20chess'%20enfant%20terrible%2C%20of%20cheating%20in%20a%20tournament.%20What%20followed%20was%20a%20breathless%20debate%20(not%20by%20Carlsen)%20over%20whether%20Niemann%20had%20managed%20this%20with%20a%20device%20hidden%20in%20a%20particularly%20intimate%20part%20of%20his%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chess%20tournament%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663946fbb8f515beaf120781%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChess%3Cp%3EDean%20Mouhtaropoulos%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20consensus%20among%20serious%20chess%20players%20is%20that%20the%20specific%20allegation%20is%20absurd%2C%C2%A0but%20paranoia%20about%20cheating%20pervades%20the%20game%2C%20from%20grandmasters%20playing%20in%20tournaments%20to%20amateurs%20whacking%20away%20at%20each%20other%20online.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FChess.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChess.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20bans%2090%2C000-odd%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chess.com%2Ffair-play%23fair-play-numbers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplayers%20every%20month%20for%20cheating%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20understand%20why.%20I've%20cheated%20at%20chess.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYears%20ago%20I%20periodically%20played%20online%20against%20a%20college%20buddy.%20He%20beat%20me%2C%20a%20lot.%20So%20in%20one%20or%20two%20games%2C%20purely%20out%20of%20curiosity%2C%20I%20booted%20up%20a%20chess%20engine%2C%20plugged%20in%20the%20moves%20he%20made%2C%20responded%20with%20the%20computer-determined%20optimal%20moves%2C%20and%20won%20handily.%20I%20told%20him%20promptly%20what%20I'd%20done.%20But%20there%20was%20also%20a%20prurient%20little%20thrill%20to%20winning%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20undeserved.%20And%20I'm%20hardly%20the%20only%20one%20who%20feels%20this%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChess%20is%20an%20extraordinarily%20easy%20game%20to%20cheat%20at.%20Computer%20programs%20have%20handily%20beaten%20human%20players%20ever%20since%20Deep%20Blue%20versus%20Kasparov%20in%201997.%20And%20there's%20no%20easy%20remedy.%20At%20the%20most%20basic%20level%2C%20there's%20the%20risk%20of%20people%20copying%20computer%20moves%20by%20rote%2C%20but%20that's%20relatively%20straightforward%20to%20detect.%20For%20more%20sophisticated%20players%2C%20cheating%20on%20a%20single%20move%20at%20the%20right%20moment%20is%20sometimes%20enough%20to%20give%20them%20the%20edge.%20Even%20just%20a%20signal%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20cough%2C%20a%20gesture%2C%20a%20vibration%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0that%20their%20seemingly%20innocuous%20next%20move%20will%20actually%20be%20critical%2C%20even%20if%20they're%20not%20told%20what%20the%20right%20move%20is%2C%20can%20be%20enough%20to%20make%20a%20player%20slow%20down%20and%20find%20the%20pathway%20to%20the%20(ill-gotten)%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHence%20a%20constant%20fear%20of%20cheaters%20and%20a%20string%20of%20minor%20scandals.%20The%20former%20world%20champion%20Vladimir%20Kramnik%20has%20in%20recent%20years%20repeatedly%20cast%20aspersions%20on%20other%20high-profile%20players%2C%20including%20Nakamura.%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FChess.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChess.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20subsequently%20said%20it%20investigated%20%26quot%3Bdozens%20of%20players%26quot%3B%20whose%20play%20Kramnik%20had%20questioned%20and%20found%20no%20evidence%20%26quot%3Bin%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20cases.%26quot%3B)%20The%20grandmaster%20Fabiano%20Caruana%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DADK1o1sZ0s0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20a%20recent%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he'd%20%26quot%3Bbet%20a%20lot%26quot%3B%20that%20someone%20in%20the%20top%2010%20players%20had%20cheated%20at%20some%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20concern%20can%20taint%20players'%20enjoyment%20of%20the%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20just%20sucks%20because%20you're%20trying%20your%20hardest%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20it%20kind%20of%20doesn't%20matter%20because%20you're%20just%20playing%20god%2C%20essentially%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dan%20Timbrell%2C%20a%2033-year-old%20working%20in%20machine%20learning%20in%20the%20Netherlands.%20%26quot%3BYou%20are%20pulling%20your%20heart%20and%20soul%20into%20really%20trying%20to%20win%20a%20game%2C%20and%20then%20you%20just%20realize%20it%20is%20just%20punching%20a%20brick%20wall.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20four%20months%2C%20I%20played%20a%20shit%20ton%20of%20chess%2C%20and%20I%20learned%20a%20lot%20by%20being%20summarily%20beaten%20by%20nearly%20every%20person%20I%20talked%20to.%20But%20I%20also%20felt%20more%20and%20more%20burned%20out%20by%20the%20game.%20I%20found%20myself%20constantly%20fretting%20about%20my%20Elo%20rating.%20It%20distracted%20from%20what%20actually%20mattered%3A%C2%A0the%20chess.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChess%20is%20a%20notoriously%20brutal%20game%20for%20the%20ego.%20If%20you%20lose%2C%20it's%20simply%20because%20you%20weren't%20good%20enough.%20Chess%20is%20a%20skill%20that%20can%20be%20learned%2C%20like%20any%20other%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20stop%20people%20online%20from%20discussing%20ad%20nauseam%20whether%20there's%20a%20correlation%20between%20chess%20prowess%20and%20IQ.%20Add%20internet-tracked%20Elo%20ratings%2C%20and%20you've%20got%20a%20potent%20recipe%20for%20an%20inferiority%20complex.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%2027-year-old%20musician%20in%20New%20York%20City%20who%20got%20into%20chess%20after%20watching%20%26quot%3BThe%20Queen's%20Gambit%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20me%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20either%20make%20good%20moves%20or%20bad%20moves.%20So%20it's%20very%20easy%20to%20say%2C%20'Oh%20my%2C%20I've%20made%20a%20terrible%20move%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0I'm%20so%20stupid.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20could%20relate.%20When%20I%20was%20playing%20online%2C%20I%20began%20gravitating%20toward%20anonymous%2C%20logged-out%20games%20%E2%80%94%20a%20far%20more%20relaxed%20affair.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChess'%20problems%20aren't%20unique.%20But%20it%20is%20uniquely%20positioned%20to%20act%20as%20an%20accelerant%20for%20the%20internet's%20worst%20impulses%3A%20sexism%2C%20abuse%2C%20cheating%2C%20elitism%2C%20and%20toxic%20nerdery.%20It's%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20what%20Juliana%20Gallin%20described%20to%20me%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20stunning%2C%20breathtaking%20beauty%20and%20magic%20of%20chess.%26quot%3B%20My%20most%20memorable%20chess%20experiences%2C%20the%20places%20where%20I%20encountered%20that%20magic%2C%20weren't%20online.%20They%20were%20playing%20in%20the%20crowded%20thrill%20of%20Club%20Chess%20in%20New%20York%2C%20or%20trading%20pieces%20with%20a%20buddy%20over%20a%20gin%20and%20tonic%20in%20a%20Lake%20Tahoe%20cabin%2C%20or%20battling%20it%20out%20in%20the%20cafeteria%20of%20a%20Russian%20bathhouse%20in%20San%20Francisco.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20was%20wrapping%20up%20this%20story%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D26174PF9Gmw%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYouTube%20recommended%20me%20a%20video%20by%20ChessPage1%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20janky%20instructional%20channel.%20At%20the%20high%20levels%2C%20the%20robotic-sounding%20voice%20said%2C%20players%20need%20an%20encyclopedic%20knowledge%20of%20openings%20and%20theory%20and%20a%20grand%20strategy%20to%20execute.%20But%20among%20us%20mortals%2C%20people%20screw%20up%20in%20minor%20ways%20several%20times%20a%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can%20be%20the%20guy%20who%20just%20doesn't%20blunder%20and%20also%20spots%20the%20opponent's%20blunders%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20voice%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20can%20easily%20become%20a%20very%20good%20chess%20player%20without%20having%20to%20pull%20off%20some%20complex%20mastery%20game%20plan%20%E2%80%A6%20You%20don't%20have%20a%20game%20plan%2C%20your%20opponent%20doesn't%20have%20a%20game%20plan%2C%20everybody%20is%20confused.%20But%20confusion%20means%20high%20probability%20of%20blunders%2C%20and%20if%20you%20don't%20blunder%2C%20you%20will%20crush%2099%25%20of%20your%20opponents.%20Congratulations%2C%20you%20are%20now%20enlightened%20and%20smart.%26quot%3B%20They%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BRemember%2C%C2%A0whenever%20you%20feel%20like%20you%20need%20a%20complex%20strategy%2C%20%3Cem%3Ejust%20don't%20blunder%3C%2Fem%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20good%20advice%20for%20chess%2C%20and%20for%20life.%20If%20in%20doubt%2C%20remember%20that%20basically%20no%20one%20else%20has%20it%20figured%20out%20either.%20Just%20try%20not%20to%20screw%20up%20too%20badly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Frob-price%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ERob%20Price%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20for%20Business%20Insider%20and%20writes%20features%20and%20investigations%20about%20the%20technology%20industry.%20His%20Signal%20number%20is%20%2B1%20650-636-6268%2C%20and%20his%20email%20is%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Arprice%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Erprice%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%