3ETo%20boost%20the%20process%20of%20germination%20and%20prevent%20future%20pest%20attacks%20and%20root%20diseases%2C%20Dr%20Naveen%20advises%20treating%20seeds%20with%20organic%20fertilisers%20and%20insecticides.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CInstead%20of%20water%2C%20soak%20seeds%20in%20%3Cem%3Epanchgavya%20%3C%2Fem%3E(organic%20concoction%20prepared%20by%20mixing%20five%20items%20obtained%20from%20cow%20like%20urine%2C%20ghee%2C%20dung%2C%20milk%2C%20and%20curd)%20for%20half%20an%20hour.%20Dry%20these%20seeds%20for%20an%20hour%20in%20a%20semi-shade%20area.%20These%20seeds%20will%20be%20ready%20for%20sowing%20the%20next%20day.%20If%20you%20do%20not%20have%20%3Cem%3Epanchgavya%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eyou%20can%20use%20five%20to%20seven%20days%20old%20buttermilk%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20germination%20process%2C%20he%20says%2C%20differs%20for%20various%20vegetables.%20For%20instance%2C%20tomato%20seeds%20will%20germinate%20within%20seven%20days%2C%20brinjals%20within%2010%20days%2C%20chillies%20within%2014%20days%2C%20radish%20within%20four%20to%20five%20days%2C%20and%20spinach%20within%20three%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFertiliser%20from%20fish%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20than%20%3Cem%3Epanchgavya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Ejeevamrita%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20vermicompost%2C%20Dr%20Naveen%20prepares%20a%20unique%20organic%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F338660%2Fhow-to-grow-fruits-on-terrace-gardening-tips-visakhapatnam-woman-wins-award%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efertiliser%20using%20fish%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20boost%20plant%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2FChennai-dr-naveen-4-1714627724.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr%20Naveen%