ally%20good%20for%20homes.%20They%20bring%20in%20more%20shade%20in%20the%20house%2C%20they%20look%20authentic%20and%20the%20sun%20is%20never%20hitting%20the%20entire%20roof%20at%20one%20time.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ENatural%20materials%20make%20a%20cooler%20home%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20materials%2C%20the%20three%20architects%20agree%20that%20using%20natural%20materials%20can%20bring%20down%20the%20temperatures%20significantly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CStudy%20the%20area%20well%20before%20you%20start%20constructing%20your%20home.%20By%20knowing%20the%20area%20well%2C%20you%20can%20find%20natural%20and%20traditional%20materials%20to%20build%20your%20home.%20Mangalore%20tiles%20are%20something%20that%20I%20recommend%20to%20all%20my%20clients.%20These%20tiles%20are%20very%20durable%20and%20breathable.%20A%20Mangalore%20tiled%20roof%20is%20not%20concrete%20and%20has%20space%20for%20cross%20ventilation%20letting%20the%20house%20breathe%2C%E2%80%9D%20George%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsing%20materials%20such%20as%20wood%20and%20stones%20for%20construction%20instead%20of%20cement%20can%20also%20do%20wonders%20for%20the%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAgain%2C%20I%20would%20emphasise%20the%20use%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F348313%2Falwar-zero-cement-sustainable-home-rainwater-harvesting-neem-jaggery-built-by-shipra-singhania%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraditional%20materials%20such%20as%20mud%2C%20straw%20and%20lime%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20make%20homes.%20Mud%20is%20a%20natural%20coolant%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20turning%20towards%20mud%20homes.%20Additionally%2C%20using%20lime%20on%20the%20floor%20or%20the%20walls%20can%20also%20help%20you%20bring%20down%20the%20temperature%20of%20the%20house%20significantly%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Shipra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFor%20existing%20apartments%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20a%20home%20that%20is%20already%20constructed%20and%20has%20no%20scope%20for%20reconstruction%2C%20there%20are%20some%20%3Cem%3Ejugaads%20(quick%20fixes)%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20these%20architects%20have%20suggested.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2Fmud-house--1702472206.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Using%20materials%20such%20as%20mud%2C%20straw%20and%20lime%20can%20keep%20the%20house%20naturally%20cool.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2Fmud-house--1702472206.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2Fmud-house--1702472206-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2Fmud-house--1702472206-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2Fmud-house--1702472206-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2Fmud-house--1702472206-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-335983%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EUsing%20materials%20such%20as%20mud%2C%20straw%20and%20lime%20can%20keep%20the%20house%20naturally%20cool.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20Consider%20building%20a%20small%20terrace%20garden%20for%20increased%20greenery%20and%20shade%20in%20the%20home%2C%20suggests%20George.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20You%20can%20also%20consider%20painting%20your%20roof%20white%20so%20that%20it%20reflects%20some%20of%20the%20heat.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20quite%20effective%20and%20I%20have%20done%20it%20in%20my%20own%20home%20too%2C%E2%80%9D%20George%20shares.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20Sherpa%20advises%20using%20%3Cem%3EKhus%20(%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20native%20Indian%20grass%20which%20has%20traditionally%20been%20used%20as%20a%20coolant%20in%20Indian%20households)%20or%20any%20dried%20grass%20sheet%2C%20the%20ones%20that%20are%20typically%20used%20in%20coolers%20on%20your%20windows.%20If%20you%20water%20them%2C%20the%20wind%20that%20comes%20through%20them%20will%20be%20cooler.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4.%20You%20can%20also%20use%20terracotta%20coolers%20that%20many%20innovators%20have%20made%20to%20keep%20the%20home%20cool%20as%20they%20are%20more%20sustainable%20in%20nature.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E5.%20One%20important%20principle%20that%20is%20often%20ignored%20in%20practice%20is%20that%20there%20is%20no%20%E2%80%98one-size-fits-all%E2%80%99%20solution.%20%E2%80%9CMost%20regions%20have%20traditional%20techniques%20for%20passive%20cooling%20that%20are%20often%20overlooked%20by%20modern%20architecture%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Ayesha%20Jhunjhunwala%2C%20an%20architect%20and%20director%20of%20Coonoor%20Estates.%20You%20can%20consider%20trying%20out%20traditional%20methods%20to%20cool%20your%20home%2C%20she%20advises.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20in%20hot%2C%20dry%20climates%20such%20as%20Rajasthan%2C%20a%20layer%20of%20inverted%20mud%20pots%20on%20the%20roof%20of%20a%20structure%20can%20significantly%20reduce%20the%20temperature%20of%20the%20building.%20This%20effect%20is%20strongest%20when%20the%20pots%20are%20painted%20white%20to%20increase%20the%20amount%20of%20sunlight%20reflected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714487577000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F71e1f2ce8e654135b509da9fba6c6619_311592766_142412935197808_3738696823372802622_n-1680175563.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D348728%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20soaring%20temperatur